(
<figureCitation id="133D859FFFE6174CA548FA4259DCFA2C" box="[1076,1193,1497,1522]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="1.[162,241,1151,1173]" captionTargetBox="[168,1439,199,1109]" captionTargetId="figure-337@1.[163,1443,195,1112]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figure 1. Lateral habitus of some Colletinae showing some of their diversity. A–P, females, Hemicotelles magallanes (A), H. ruizii (B), Mourecotelles mixtus (C), Mourecotelles sp.1 (D), Xanthocotelles atacama (E), X. fritzi (F), Colletes cyanescens (G), C. cyaniventris (H), C. fulvipes (I), C. halophilus (J), C. nigritulus (K), C. petropolitanus (L), C. rugicollis (M), C. slevini (N), C. solidaginis (O) and C. zuluensis (P). Scale bars = 1 mm." pageId="11" pageNumber="210">FIG. 1A, B</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB9991AFFE6174CA247F9B9584BF9E8" blockId="11.[827,1342,1569,1591]" box="[827,1342,1569,1591]" pageId="11" pageNumber="210">
<emphasis id="B9724508FFE6174CA247F9B95EBEF9E9" box="[827,971,1570,1591]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="210">
<typeStatus id="54BD27B8FFE6174CA247F9B95E05F9E9" box="[827,880,1570,1591]" pageId="11" pageNumber="210">Type</typeStatus>
species:
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C06E299FFE6174CA2ABF9BA584CF9E8" authority="Herbst, 1923" authorityName="Herbst" authorityYear="1923" box="[983,1337,1569,1591]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Lonchopria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruizii">
<emphasis id="B9724508FFE6174CA2ABF9BA59E8F9E9" box="[983,1181,1569,1591]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="210">Lonchopria ruizii</emphasis>
Herbst, 1923
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB9991AFFE6174BA247F9FB5FE9FC07" blockId="11.[827,1443,1632,1899]" lastBlockId="12.[145,762,196,986]" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="211" pageId="11" pageNumber="210">
<emphasis id="B9724508FFE6174CA247F9FB5EC9F9AB" box="[827,956,1632,1653]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="210">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Females of 
<taxonomicName id="4C06E299FFE6174CA527F9FB5983F9AB" authorityName="Toro &amp; Cabezas" authorityYear="1977" box="[1115,1270,1632,1653]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hemicotelles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9724508FFE6174CA527F9FB5983F9AB" box="[1115,1270,1632,1653]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="210">Hemicotelles</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be easily differentiated from those of the other genera of 
<taxonomicName id="4C06E299FFE6174CA247F9065EC0F96D" authorityName="Lepeletier de Saint Fargeau" authorityYear="1841" box="[827,949,1693,1715]" pageId="11" pageNumber="199" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Colletinae">Colletinae</taxonomicName>
by T6 with a posteromedial longitudinal ridge (this study; Supporting Information, Fig. S11B) [T6 with a posteromedial protrusion that can be either weak and rounded (Supporting Information, Fig. S11C) or strong and subtriangular (Supporting Information, Fig. S11D) in 
<taxonomicName id="4C06E299FFE6174CA516F8AD587BF895" authorityName="Toro &amp; Cabezas" authorityYear="1978" box="[1130,1294,1846,1867]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Xanthocotelles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9724508FFE6174CA516F8AD587BF895" box="[1130,1294,1846,1867]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="210">Xanthocotelles</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and T6 with no modification (Supporting Information, Fig. S9A–C) in 
<taxonomicName id="4C06E299FFE1174BA1CCFF5E5C7EFF04" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[176,267,197,218]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9724508FFE1174BA1CCFF5E5C7EFF04" box="[176,267,197,218]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="211">Colletes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C06E299FFE1174BA03AFF5E5C91FF04" authorityName="Toro &amp; Cabezas" authorityYear="1977" box="[326,484,197,218]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Mourecotelles" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9724508FFE1174BA03AFF5E5C91FF04" box="[326,484,197,218]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="211">Mourecotelles</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
]. Males of 
<taxonomicName id="4C06E299FFE1174BA31AFF5E5F8CFF04" authorityName="Toro &amp; Cabezas" authorityYear="1977" box="[614,761,197,218]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hemicotelles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9724508FFE1174BA31AFF5E5F8CFF04" box="[614,761,197,218]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="211">Hemicotelles</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are diagnosed through the following combination of characteristics: apical mandibular tooth much longer than preapical tooth (this study; Supporting Information, Fig. S15A), legs dark-brown to black (modified from: 
<bibRefCitation id="EF97E4EBFFE1174BA03FFEC45F4DFEAA" author="Toro H &amp; Cabezas V" box="[323,568,350,372]" pageId="12" pageNumber="211" pagination="131 - 148" refId="ref13033" refString="Toro H, Cabezas V. 1978. Nuevos generos y especies de Colletini sudamericanos (Apoidea Colletidae). Segunda parte. Anales del Museo de Historia Natural de Valpariso 11: 131 - 148." type="journal article" year="1978">Toro &amp; Cabezas, 1978</bibRefCitation>
; see also 
<figureCitation id="133D859FFFE1174BA3DEFEC55DD6FE4D" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="1.[162,241,1151,1173]" captionTargetBox="[168,1439,199,1109]" captionTargetId="figure-337@1.[163,1443,195,1112]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figure 1. Lateral habitus of some Colletinae showing some of their diversity. A–P, females, Hemicotelles magallanes (A), H. ruizii (B), Mourecotelles mixtus (C), Mourecotelles sp.1 (D), Xanthocotelles atacama (E), X. fritzi (F), Colletes cyanescens (G), C. cyaniventris (H), C. fulvipes (I), C. halophilus (J), C. nigritulus (K), C. petropolitanus (L), C. rugicollis (M), C. slevini (N), C. solidaginis (O) and C. zuluensis (P). Scale bars = 1 mm." pageId="12" pageNumber="211">Fig. 1A, B</figureCitation>
) and horizontal surface of T1 much shorter than T2 (modified from: 
<bibRefCitation id="EF97E4EBFFE1174BA032FE075F74FE6F" author="Michener CD" box="[334,513,412,434]" pageId="12" pageNumber="211" pagination="22 - 703" refId="ref12360" refString="Michener CD. 1989. Classification of American Colletinae (Hymenoptera, Apoidea). University of Kansas Science Bulletin 53: 22 - 703." type="journal article" year="1989">Michener, 1989</bibRefCitation>
; see also Supporting Information, Fig. S12C) [apical tooth only slightly longer than preapical one (Supporting Information, Fig. S15B) in 
<taxonomicName id="4C06E299FFE1174BA04DFE635CBBFDD3" authorityName="Toro &amp; Cabezas" authorityYear="1977" box="[305,462,504,525]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Mourecotelles" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9724508FFE1174BA04DFE635CBBFDD3" box="[305,462,504,525]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="211">Mourecotelles</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, legs pale-yellow to darkorange (
<figureCitation id="133D859FFFE1174BA18EFD8D5C13FDF2" box="[242,358,534,556]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="1.[162,241,1151,1173]" captionTargetBox="[168,1439,199,1109]" captionTargetId="figure-337@1.[163,1443,195,1112]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figure 1. Lateral habitus of some Colletinae showing some of their diversity. A–P, females, Hemicotelles magallanes (A), H. ruizii (B), Mourecotelles mixtus (C), Mourecotelles sp.1 (D), Xanthocotelles atacama (E), X. fritzi (F), Colletes cyanescens (G), C. cyaniventris (H), C. fulvipes (I), C. halophilus (J), C. nigritulus (K), C. petropolitanus (L), C. rugicollis (M), C. slevini (N), C. solidaginis (O) and C. zuluensis (P). Scale bars = 1 mm." pageId="12" pageNumber="211">Fig. 1E, F</figureCitation>
) in 
<taxonomicName id="4C06E299FFE1174BA0E4FD8D5F37FDF5" authorityName="Toro &amp; Cabezas" authorityYear="1978" box="[408,578,534,555]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Xanthocotelles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9724508FFE1174BA0E4FD8D5F37FDF5" box="[408,578,534,555]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="211">Xanthocotelles</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and horizontal surface of T1 subequal in length to T2 (Supporting Information, Fig. S12D) in 
<taxonomicName id="4C06E299FFE1174BA0B5FDCF5F57FDB7" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[457,546,596,617]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9724508FFE1174BA0B5FDCF5F57FDB7" box="[457,546,596,617]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="211">Colletes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
]. 
<taxonomicName id="4C06E299FFE1174BA344FDCF5FBCFDB7" authorityName="Toro &amp; Cabezas" authorityYear="1977" box="[568,713,596,617]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hemicotelles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9724508FFE1174BA344FDCF5FBCFDB7" box="[568,713,596,617]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="211">Hemicotelles</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be further distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C06E299FFE1174BA378FDE95F14FD59" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[516,609,626,647]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9724508FFE1174BA378FDE95F14FD59" box="[516,609,626,647]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="211">Colletes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by forewing with a straight second recurrent vein in both sexes (modified from: 
<bibRefCitation id="EF97E4EBFFE1174BA01EFD2B5F0AFD1B" author="Toro H &amp; Cabezas V" box="[354,639,688,710]" pageId="12" pageNumber="211" pagination="45 - 64" refId="ref13000" refString="Toro H, Cabezas V. 1977. Nuevos generos y especies de Colletini sudamericanos, segunda parte. Anales del Museo de Historia Natural de Valpariso 10: 45 - 64." type="journal article" year="1977">Toro &amp; Cabezas, 1977</bibRefCitation>
; see also 
<figureCitation id="133D859FFFE1174BA1EDFD555D90FD3A" box="[145,229,718,740]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="3.[163,242,1397,1419]" captionTargetBox="[323,1283,195,1357]" captionTargetId="figure-203@3.[323,1283,195,1357]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 3. Diagnostic features of Colletinae. Numbers shown in red indicate derived character states. A–D, lateral view of male forewing, Hexantheda entrerriana (A), Hemicotelles ruizii (B), C. albomaculatus (C) and C. rufipes (D); E, F, dorsal view of female metasomal apex, C. gilvus (E) and Bicolletes rufiventris (F). Scale bars = 1 mm." pageId="12" pageNumber="211">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
) [forewing with second recurrent vein either sigmoidal (
<figureCitation id="133D859FFFE1174BA067FD765C00FCDC" box="[283,373,749,771]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="3.[163,242,1397,1419]" captionTargetBox="[323,1283,195,1357]" captionTargetId="figure-203@3.[323,1283,195,1357]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 3. Diagnostic features of Colletinae. Numbers shown in red indicate derived character states. A–D, lateral view of male forewing, Hexantheda entrerriana (A), Hemicotelles ruizii (B), C. albomaculatus (C) and C. rufipes (D); E, F, dorsal view of female metasomal apex, C. gilvus (E) and Bicolletes rufiventris (F). Scale bars = 1 mm." pageId="12" pageNumber="211">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
) or slightly arcuate outwardly (
<figureCitation id="133D859FFFE1174BA1E5FC975D9FFCFF" box="[153,234,780,802]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="3.[163,242,1397,1419]" captionTargetBox="[323,1283,195,1357]" captionTargetId="figure-203@3.[323,1283,195,1357]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 3. Diagnostic features of Colletinae. Numbers shown in red indicate derived character states. A–D, lateral view of male forewing, Hexantheda entrerriana (A), Hemicotelles ruizii (B), C. albomaculatus (C) and C. rufipes (D); E, F, dorsal view of female metasomal apex, C. gilvus (E) and Bicolletes rufiventris (F). Scale bars = 1 mm." pageId="12" pageNumber="211">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
) in 
<taxonomicName id="4C06E299FFE1174BA06BFC975C1AFCFF" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[279,367,780,801]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9724508FFE1174BA06BFC975C1AFCFF" box="[279,367,780,801]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="211">Colletes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
]; and from both 
<taxonomicName id="4C06E299FFE1174BA351FC975FB2FCFF" authorityName="Toro &amp; Cabezas" authorityYear="1977" box="[557,711,780,801]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Mourecotelles" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9724508FFE1174BA351FC975FB2FCFF" box="[557,711,780,801]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="211">Mourecotelles</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C06E299FFE1174BA1EDFCB15C42FCE1" authorityName="Toro &amp; Cabezas" authorityYear="1978" box="[145,311,810,831]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Xanthocotelles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9724508FFE1174BA1EDFCB15C42FCE1" box="[145,311,810,831]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="211">Xanthocotelles</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by subhorizontal and vertical surfaces of the metapostnotum separated from each other by a transverse carina, albeit broadly interrupted medially in both sexes (modified from: 
<bibRefCitation id="EF97E4EBFFE1174BA098FC1D5FE7FC45" author="Michener CD" box="[484,658,902,924]" pageId="12" pageNumber="211" pagination="22 - 703" refId="ref12360" refString="Michener CD. 1989. Classification of American Colletinae (Hymenoptera, Apoidea). University of Kansas Science Bulletin 53: 22 - 703." type="journal article" year="1989">Michener, 1989</bibRefCitation>
; see also 
